---
name: scljet-sql-index-multi-cond
description: SclJet index use in a multi-condition AND — seek one indexable condition, filter the rest; matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet index use in a multi-condition WHERE

A single-table query whose WHERE is one AND-group with several conditions now uses an index when
*any* condition is indexable: `pointLookup` seeks that condition (a row satisfying the whole AND also
satisfies each condition, so the seek returns a superset) and `finishRows` applies the full WHERE to
filter down. Covers an indexed column + a non-indexed predicate (`dept='eng' AND active=1`), a rowid
seek + a residual predicate (`id=4 AND dept='eng'`), the indexable condition appearing second
(`active=1 AND dept='eng'` seeks `dept`), and `COUNT`. Every result matches reference sqlite3
(verified out-of-band); locked across `[int, js]`.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, executeMutation, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def apply(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): ByteSlice =
  executeMutation(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) =>
      println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
      db
    case Right(next) => next

def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, dept TEXT, active INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(9L), SqlText("x"), SqlInteger(0L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db0) =>
    val d1 = apply(db0, "DELETE FROM t")
    val d2 = apply(d1, "CREATE INDEX idx_dept ON t(dept)")
    val db = apply(d2, "INSERT INTO t VALUES (1,'eng',1),(2,'sales',1),(3,'eng',0),(4,'eng',1),(5,'sales',0)")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM t WHERE dept = 'eng' AND active = 1 ORDER BY id")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM t WHERE id = 4 AND dept = 'eng'")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM t WHERE active = 1 AND dept = 'eng' ORDER BY id")
    show(db, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM t WHERE dept = 'sales' AND active = 0")
```
